From: Michal Kubecek <mkubecek@suse.cz>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 00:53:38 +0200
Subject: kabi: revert kabi breaking changes from bsc#1264610 fix
Patch-mainline: Never, kabi workaround
References: CVE-2026-43198 bsc#1264610

Backport of mainline commit 858d2a4f67ff ("tcp: fix potential race in
tcp_v6_syn_recv_sock()") adds new parameter to ->syn_recv_sock() callback
in struct inet_connection_sock_af_ops.

This parameter itself is a function which serves the only purpose: to be
called at the right place in tcp_v4_syn_recv_sock() if not null. However,

  - it is only used to be called if not null
  - it is not used in any other ->syn_recv_sock() callback
  - it is only not null when called from tcp_v6_syn_recv_sock()
  - tcp_v6_syn_recv_sock() calls tcp_v4_syn_recv_sock() directly
    (not via ops structure pointer)

Therefore we can restore kABI by

  - reverting changes to ->syn_recv_sock() parameter list
  - renaming patched tcp_v4_syn_recv_sock() to a different name
  - making tcp_v4_syn_recv_sock() a wrapper which calls patched with null
  - call the patched function from tcp_v6_syn_recv_sock() instead

This preserves kABI and behaviour of all ->syn_recv_sock() callbacks while
allowing tcp_v6_syn_recv_sock() call the patched function which calls
tcp_v6_mapped_child_init() if needed (when TCPv4 connection is received on
an IPv6 listening socket).

Signed-off-by: Michal Kubecek <mkubecek@suse.cz>
Reviewed-by: Petr Pavlu <petr.pavlu@suse.com>
